## Required: Justify Your Work Before Completing

Before you finalize your output, you MUST use the `call_controller` tool to open a justification dialogue with the controller. Do NOT return your final result until the controller has reviewed and approved your work.

The controller will review your justification and either approve, ask follow-up questions, or request changes. Continue the dialogue until the controller approves. Only then should you return your final structured result.

This is mandatory — returning a result without controller approval will be rejected at the phase gate.
